&gt; &gt; Perhaps we&#39;d react differently if you participated here more often--
&gt; &gt; posting your own files and asking questions of researchers. For
&gt; &gt; example, &quot;Hey, Ann--that file you just posted, I hear what you do,
&gt; &gt; but is anything clipped out of it? I think I hear a track silenced,
&gt; &gt; too. If so, why did you do that?&quot; Then I get to answer and explain
&gt; &gt; why I did it that way, offer the raw clip, or whatever. It doesn&#39;t
&gt; &gt; come off as a broad attack--just a friendly question. Even Bruce
&gt; &gt; wouldn&#39;t rip out your living eyeballs for that. (Well... maybe he
&gt; &gt; wouldn&#39;t, anyway. ;) )
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I agree with your search for The Truth. I really do. That&#39;s why you
&gt; &gt; see me get all rough-and-tumble over stuff like the Luminator when I
&gt; &gt; think it is it lacking convincing evidence. But it&#39;s waaaaaay too
&gt; &gt; early in &quot;boxology&quot; to try to make it perform as a pet circus  
&gt; animal.
&gt; &gt; Hell, we&#39;ve been studying traditional EVP for 30 years and it still
&gt; &gt; won&#39;t perform on cue for the scientists or anyone else. But if you
&gt; &gt; just listen to what you get on your own and what all the others are
&gt; &gt; getting, it becomes very clear indeed that a real phenomenon is
&gt; &gt; occurring. Sure, some things we get that we think are paranormal may
&gt; &gt; be just radio fragments, but one radio fragment does not negate all
&gt; &gt; box communication. One tweaked clip is not indicative of a  
&gt; culture of
&gt; &gt; researcher deceit. One &quot;I am Bazoozoo! Time to fry, foolish mortal!&quot;
&gt; &gt; does not mean that the RS hacks are pathways to Satan&#39;s indoor
&gt; &gt; plumbing. There are no easy answers yet--and there may never be any.
&gt; &gt; And I&#39;m not sure we&#39;re at the stage yet where we have the right to
&gt; &gt; demand The Truth or whether we would even see it if it was  
&gt; staring us
&gt; &gt; in the face.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; All right, enough joy in myself one-hand clapping.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; LC is right that if you want to try to pursue this in the way you
&gt; &gt; want to pursue it, then you need to find some people who share your
&gt; &gt; mindset and go to it. I don&#39;t think you&#39;re going to find those  
&gt; people
&gt; &gt; here, necessarily--at least among the old guard. We&#39;re the beatniks
&gt; &gt; in black leather, smoking ciggies and reading bad poetry to the beat
&gt; &gt; of bongos, HMO.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Ann
